1:5](../../../bib/kjv/rev001.htm#005.md); The plague of leprosy was
inflicted immediately from the hand of God, and came not from natural
causes, as other diseases; and therefore must be managed according to a
divine law. Miriam's leprosy, and Gehazi's and King Uzziah's were all
the punishments of particular sins; and if generally it was so, no
marvel there was so much care taken to distinguish it from a common
distemper, that none might be looked upon as lying under this
extraordinary token of Divine displeasure, but those that really were
so.

